The ILL high-flux reactor
.Below 1.5 MeV, only the Gams 2/3 data were used.
Between 1.5 and 2 MeV, a weighted average of the two
data sets has been taken. Above 2 MeV, only the pair
spectrometer data have been used. Below 300 KeV, the
data from this work and from Backlin et al., Nuclear
Phys. A380 (1982) 189, were used using a weighted
average. Absolute energy calibration was obtained from
transitions measured with the gams4 spectrometer.
.The data were compared with (D,P) and (D,T) data
from the munich tandem accelerator. Primary gamma
rays following average resonance capture were
observed at the institute for nuclear research in
kiev. Summed coincidence measurements were carried
out at the Dubna IBR-30 reactor.
.The bent-crystal spectrometer Gams 2/3 was used up
to 2.5 MeV gamma rays. The resolution was about 300 eV
at 1 MeV. The pair spectrometer pn4, consisting of
a Ge(Li) detector and two Na-I detectors was used from
1.2 to 8.5 MeV, with a resolution of 5 KeV at 8 MeV.
Eight transitions were measured with the ultra-high
resolution gamma spectrometer GAMS4.
.Statistical errors.
The ILL high-flux reactor
.Thermal neutrons. The sample was irradiated with a
thermal neutron flux of 5e+14 neutrons/cm2/sec.
In-beam gamma spectroscopy.
.Gadolinium oxide targets, enriched to 90 percent in
Gd-155. Two targets, 2 and 20 mg/cm2, were used.
